Privacy policy
Data Protection Privacy Policy
At Kitronik we take the protection of our customers’ personal details very seriously. It goes without saying that we will never sell on your details and we only share them with a small number of companies essential to providing the service. The type of information we keep and what it is used for depends on why you gave us the data in the first place, as detailed in the paragraphs below.
Kitronik may change this policy from time to time by updating this page. You should check this page from time to time to ensure that you are happy with any changes. This policy is effective from 1/11/2010.
Placing an order
If you have placed an order online then Kitronik store the details of what was on the order, the delivery address and your contact details as this is all required so we can meet the contractual requirements of fulfilling the order. Your address and contact information will be shared with the Royal Mail or our preferred courier in order that we can ship the order. Your email address will be used to confirm the order and to inform you that the goods are on the way. We will only use your phone number if we have a query with the order.
If you have checked out without creating an account we store these details for 12 months allowing refunds or replacement under warrantee to be an easy experience and so that we can contact you should we need to recall a product that you have purchased. At the end of the 12 months all your personal details are erased, we still know what products were sold, but we don’t know anything about the buyer.
If you have created an account then the details of your order are stored for a period of 3 years so that you can look back at your order history, should you wish to reorder.
If you have a credit account or distributor account with us then we also keep the order history for a period of 3 years.
Email list
If you have signed up to our email list then your email address is stored by MailChimp and is only used in order that we can keep you up to date. You can withdraw from this service at any point in time by clicking the unsubscribe link at the bottom of all emails.
Paper marketing list
Most UK secondary schools receive a termly update flyer and a new catalogue once a year. This is sent to as many or as few staff members as the school likes. If you wish to change the name of the person we send it to, add a new name or stop receiving these communications please get in touch with the customer service team by phone or email.
Website
The Kitronik website runs on the Shopify platform, if you place an order with us Shopify will store your details so we can facilitate processing the order. If you make use of the stock notifications emails we use a third party app from Zooomy apps, who need to store your email so they are able to email you when the item is back in stock. Your browsing information may be shared with Google and Facebook for advertising purposes.
Website cookies
A cookie is a small file which is placed on your computer's hard drive. Cookies allow web applications to respond to you as an individual. The web application can tailor its operations to your needs, likes and dislikes by gathering and remembering information about your preferences.
We use traffic log cookies to identify which pages are being used. This helps us analyse data about web page traffic and improve our website in order to tailor it to customer needs. We only use this information for statistical analysis purposes.
We also use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this website.
Overall, cookies help us provide you with a better website, by enabling us to monitor which pages you find useful and which you do not. A cookie in no way gives us access to your computer or any information about you, other than the data you choose to share with us. You can choose to accept or decline cookies. Most web browsers automatically accept cookies, but you can usually modify your browser setting to decline cookies if you prefer. The Kitronik website relies on cookies and will not function correctly without them.
List of cookies we collect
Shopify
The Kitronik website is hosted on the Shopify platform. Shopify allows users to localise their experience using cookies to store location and currency information, logged in status is also stored in a cookie. Cookies are used to differentiate carts as well as allow the checkout process to function. Shopify logs the pages you have visited. On some product pages there is the option to buy locally, if you select your country this is remembered in a cookie.
Facebook & Google
Cookies are used by Facebook and Google to log information on which pages you have visited.
Youtube
On product or resource pages that contain a video, cookies will be used by Youtube to store session ID and preferences which are needed to allow the videos to be played.
Google Play Store apps
Kitronik collects no data or personal information from users that download this app. There is no way to create a user account from within the app, there are no in app purchases, no in app advertising, and there are no app push notifications.
The app will request permission to access Bluetooth and Location, this is used solely for app functionality. No usage data is collected or transmitted by Kitronik or a third party.
This policy applies to the following apps: Kitronik Bluetooth Control.
Security
We are committed to ensuring that your information is secure. In order to prevent unauthorised access or disclosure, we have put in place suitable physical, electronic and managerial procedures to safeguard and secure the information we collect online.
Your rights
Should you wish, you can ask to see your personal data and can request that any errors are corrected. You also have the right to withdraw your consent for us using your personal data and have the right to be forgotten. Please get in touch with the customer service team by phone or email should you wish to do any of these.
If you don’t feel that we have acted on your requests then you are entitled to make a complaint to the data protection supervisory authority.
This information has been produced by Geoff Hampson, the data controller at Kitronik. If you have any questions regarding it please
get in touch with the customer service team
, who will be glad to assist you.
Free UK Delivery*
Spend over £40 (ex VAT) and get free delivery. (excludes sheet materials and offshore / remote areas).
No Quibble Refunds
If you don't like the product for whatever reason, send it back (packaged and unused) for a full refund.
Product Support
Free Email and telephone support on all our products.
Secure Payments
Pay securely using credit / debit card or by Paypal.
